It’s actually quite a great album, better than his last 2.
It’s better than Kamikaze, which was a decent album too, but most of the songs had the same concept of going after mumble rap and critics, which brings most of the album down. There’s great songs on there, though.
Revival, which I feel is overhated (kinda), wasn’t terrible. It was just more disappointing than bad. Probably because Eminem is one of the best rappers of all time, his albums have very high expectations (at the time at least). It’s just that the album came out as underwhelming. There were a few good tracks, a few that are half/half and some really bad tracks.

snippet.textDisplay:
A couple of more listens this album really grows on you I can’t lie. But the problem is his difficult issue to grow up lol The content is there but the execution is far from perfect. If he can just write a little smarter with funnier, more wittier lines to maybe cover up those real disgusting/cringe heavy ones lol some songs might be a little more bearable. The idea and theme of the album is better than the album itself but there’s something so refreshing to hear an untraditional mainstream hiphop album out sale and out perform every other album around it while also still having a message. And that’s pretty impressive for a forty seven year old man in any genre of music to do. Especially since hiphop is considered a young man’s game. Jay Z, Royce Da 5’9 and Eminem keep proving that statement wrong time and time again. The songs that are bad on this album are really bad but the ones that are decent, good or great even,
still remind us that Eminem is not leaving us for a couple of more years and he’s still got something to say and I’m here for it. I can’t defend everything he does fuck no,
but God Damn I do respect the man. If he can just focus a bit more and study the criticism he gets with a more level head instead of just brushing it off, I think we could finally get that Eminem album that’ll have even the snarkiest of Eminem haters putting Eminem back in their top 10. But I can only hope. He’s still in my top 10. But this album isn’t the greatest. On a bad day 3/10 on a good day 5.5/10 lol 😂

still remind us that Eminem is not leaving us for a couple of more years and he’s still got something to say and I’m here for it. I can’t defend everything he does fuck no,
 but God Damn I do respect the man. If he can just focus a bit more and study the criticism he gets with a more level head instead of just brushing it off, I think we could finally get that Eminem album that’ll have even the snarkiest of Eminem haters putting Eminem back in their top 10. But I can only hope. He’s still in my top 10. But this album isn’t the greatest. On a bad day 3/10 on a good day 5.5/10 lol 😂
